<h1>Find patch or class edge cells</h1>

<p>This tool finds all grid cells in a raster image containing categorical data (i.e. classes or objects) 
that are located on the edge of patch or class features. The user must specify the name of the input image, 
which must be of a categorical data type, and the output image. Grid cells that are located along class or 
patch boundaries will be assigned their class value/patch ID. All other grid cells will be assigned a zero 
in the output image.</p>

